"title": "5242: buying and selling",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5242: buying and selling",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Buying and selling are an integral part of the everyday life of the world. Scripture makes it clear that God expects moral dealings by his people in this area of life as in every other.</p>\n<h2>Some biblical transactions</h2>\n<h3>The first recorded transaction</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:3-Gen23:4\">GEN 23:3–23:4</a></strong> <em>Many other transactions had obviously taken place before this, from the earliest times.</em></p>\n<h3>Transactions in land</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:20-Gen47:22\">GEN 47:20–47:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:3\">RUT 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:16\">PRO 31:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:9-Jer32:10\">JER 32:9–32:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:7\">MAT 27:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:18\">LUK 14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:34\">ACT 4:34</a></p>\n<h3>Buying animals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:19\">LUK 14:19</a></p>\n<h3>Buying food and drink</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:57\">GEN 41:57</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut2:28\">DEU 2:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:5\">JHN 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:29\">JHN 13:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:6\">REV 6:6</a></p>\n<h3>Transactions in other goods</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:11-Rev18:13\">REV 18:11–18:13</a></p>\n<h3>Buying of slaves</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:12\">GEN 17:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:2\">EXO 21:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:44-Lev25:45\">LEV 25:44–25:45</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:1-Hos3:2\">HOS 3:1–3:2</a></p>\n<h3>The labour market</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:39-Lev25:40\">LEV 25:39–25:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:1-Matt20:2\">MAT 20:1–20:2</a></p>\n<h2>God's standards in buying and selling</h2>\n<h3>Fairness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:5-Gen23:13\">GEN 23:5–23:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:24\">2SA 24:24</a></p>\n<h3>Honesty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:35-Lev19:36\">LEV 19:35–19:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:14-Gen23:16\">GEN 23:14–23:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13-Deut25:16\">DEU 25:13–25:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:1\">PRO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:10\">PRO 20:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:23\">PRO 20:23</a></p>\n<h2>Sins to avoid in buying and selling</h2>\n<h3>Dishonesty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:14\">PRO 20:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:5\">AMO 8:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:10-Mic6:11\">MIC 6:10–6:11</a></p>\n<h3>Greed</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:26\">PRO 11:26</a></p>\n<h3>Exploitation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:14\">LEV 25:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:4\">LAM 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:6\">AMO 8:6</a></p>\n<h3>Extravagance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:13\">LUK 15:13</a></p>\n<h3>Desecration of the Sabbath</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:31\">NEH 10:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:15-Neh13:22\">NEH 13:15–13:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:5\">AMO 8:5</a></p>\n<h3>Desecration of the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:12-Matt21:13\">MAT 21:12–21:13</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:15-Mark11:17\">MRK 11:15–11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:45-Luke19:46\">LUK 19:45–19:46</a> <em>The merchants were operating within the outer court of the temple, itself consecrated as a place of prayer and worship.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:14-John2:16\">JHN 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h3>Worldliness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:12\">EZK 7:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:29-1Cor7:31\">1CO 7:29–7:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:13\">JAS 4:13</a></p>\n<h2>Oppression through the control of buying and selling</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:16-Rev13:17\">REV 13:16–13:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Spiritual transactions</h2>\n<h3>Sinners sold to sin</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:20\">1KI 21:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:14\">ROM 7:14</a></p>\n<h3>Israel sold and redeemed</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:14\">JDG 2:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:12\">PSA 44:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:1\">ISA 43:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:1\">ISA 50:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:3\">ISA 52:3</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ has bought his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:23\">1CO 7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:1\">2PE 2:1</a></p>\n<h3>Spiritual wealth to be bought</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:23\">PRO 23:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:1\">ISA 55:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:44-Matt13:46\">MAT 13:44–13:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:9\">MAT 25:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:18\">REV 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Gifts money cannot buy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:12-Job28:19\">JOB 28:12–28:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:7-Ps49:8\">PSA 49:7–49:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:37\">MRK 8:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:20\">ACT 8:20</a></p>",
